MinValue is the smallest value that can be set
MaxValue is the highest value that can be set
Weight is a mulptlier

Text:
To visualize the CSV data using Mermaid.js Live Editor graph TD syntax, we need to know the specific contents of your CSV file. Please provide the data so I can assist you better.

However, here is a general example showing how to create a graph based on Entities, Attributes, Relations, Goals, Conditions, and Decision Variables:

```mermaid
graph TD
  subgraph entities_attributes_relations
    classStyle blue
    A[Entity1] --> B[Attribute1]
    C[Entity2] --> D[Attribute2]
    E[Entity3] --> F[Attribute3]
  
    classStyle orange
    G[Relation1] --> A
    H[Relation2] --> C
  
  subgraph goals_conditions_decision_variables
    classStyle green
    I[Goal1] --> J[Entity/Attributes]
    
    classStyle red
    K[Condition1] --> L[Entity/Attributes]
  
    classStyle purple
    M[DecisionVariable1] --> N[RelevantEntity/Attribute]
  end
```

Replace `[Entity1]`, `[Attribute1]`, etc., with the actual entities, attributes, relations, goals, conditions, and decision variables from your CSV data. Remember to use Mermaid's syntax for lines (-->), subgraphs, and styling (classStyle).
